    But it still doesn't change how incredibly WRONG the French government is on this from the American perspective.  You see, it's a moral issue.   It has nothing to do with the annoying French behavior before and after the Iraq situation.  (Of course, the French are upset now that they won't be let in now because they had lucrative contracts before.)   Once you understand this you'll be better off.    What you are doing is exactly prohibiting Freedom of Religion.   (Of course you can argue that it's not the U.S., but if you didn't think some of our ideas were good why is the Statue of Liberty standing in New York harbor and why was their a need for a particularly bloody French revolution such a short time after our own?)   We do not agree with that.  We think it's abhorrent.   <br>
